name: L
description:
Unfolding of an L sparse matrix into a lattice. The original matrix describes a 2D grid subdivision first documented by R. Diekmann and R. Preis in 1998. In this simulation, the matrix is represented as a lattice with 956 nodes which undergoes a process of unfolding until it reaches equilibrium. 

@lukapiskorec, mp4, 1000 x 1000 pix, 300 frames
